{
  "texts": [
    "In conclusion, this study assessed the accuracy and consistency on the GPT-4o, Claude 3.5 Sonnet, and Gemini 1.5 Pro in responding to diet and nutrition questions of the RD exam.",
    "In contrast to the previous LLM evaluation studies focusing on nutritional management, our experiments were not restricted to ChatGPT or ZS prompting.",
    "We evaluated the models using the RD exam and analyzed their errors across various questions complexities and nutrition domains.",
    "Our findings highlighted the strengths and weaknesses of the three LLMs, showing the influence of different prompting techniques on their responses to the RD exam questions.",
    "GPT-4o with CoT-SC prompting outperformed other approaches, while Gemini 1.5 Pro with ZS indicated the highest consistency."
  ]
}